<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
  Sample PG&E Share My Data (Green Button / ESPI) export used by ONBOARDING as the
  stand-in for a live Share My Data pull (see src/lib/onboarding/source.ts). It is a
  fresh account (Olsen Family Farms) with four service IDs the seeded sample farm does
  not use, so onboarding always imports them as new pumps:

    7720450001  Home Well   AG-C  ~110 kW   -> classifies as a pump
    7720450002  East Well   AG-C   ~95 kW   -> classifies as a pump
    7720450003  South Well  AG-B   ~72 kW   -> classifies as a pump
    7720450004  Shop Meter  B-1   ~6 kW flat -> classifies as a NON-pump (office/shop)

  The point is that auto-classification visibly separates the three big seasonal
  agricultural loads from the small flat commercial one. One billing cycle each
  (closing 2026-06-12). Each meter carries a day-spanning set of 15-minute readings,
  mult 0 (Wh): the pumps sit idle through the day then run hard in the evening (a low
  load factor, spiky), while the shop draws a small steady load all day (a high load
  factor, flat), so the shape signal is exercised, not just the tariff and peak.
  Same conventions as sandhu-multi-meter.xml; see fixtures/greenbutton/README.md.
-->
